AB  - This paper deals with the relationship between the Compound Poisson distribution, Bayesian uncertainty (or mixing) models and infinite divisibility. It is shown that the Compound Poisson distribution arises in many situations in the theory of risk. A large number of recent results are reviewed and some new results are given.
